OL,3,CThe women who were pivotal in allowing
OL,4,Cthe miners to strike
OL,6,FCarrying a banner and a box of
OL,7,Fmemories, a small group of women make
OL,8,Ftheir way into the Welfare Hall in
OL,9,FOnllwyn. Long rows of tables and
OL,10,Fchairs sit empty. The wide stage is
OL,11,Fset. This building, at the heart of
OL,12,Fthe village, hasn't changed much over
OL,13,Fthe last four decades.
OL,15,FA backdrop to community life. A
OL,16,Fconstant. A place for people to come
OL,17,Ftogether.
OL,19,FFour decades ago women in Wales were
OL,20,Fon the front line of the longest and
OL,21,FBritain has ever seen.
