OL,3,CThe women who were pivotal in allowing
OL,4,Cthe miners to strike
OL,6,FChristine Powell sorts through a box
OL,7,Fof metal pin badges. She pulls out a
OL,8,Ffew: "Coal not Dole" ,"Support the
OL,9,FMiners" and NUM enamel branch badges.
OL,10,FIn this box, lies not just messages of
OL,11,Fprotest and defiance, but a sense of
OL,12,Fidentity. A way of life.
OL,14,FIn March 1984, Christine Powell was a
OL,15,Fyoung physics teacher and newly
OL,16,Fmarried miner's wife.
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                   G2/14
