OL,3,CThe women who were pivotal in allowing
OL,4,Cthe miners to strike
OL,6,FAs the strike got underway, the pay
OL,7,Fcheques stopped and the bills piled
OL,8,Fup, so women like Christine, across
OL,9,Fthe South Wales coalfield began to
OL,10,Forganise the support their husbands
OL,11,Fand the community needed.
OL,13,FDescribing what organising the support
OL,14,Fwas like, Christine said: "So on a
OL,15,FWednesday it was organised chaos
OL,16,Fbecause there was food everywhere, in
OL,17,Fvarious vehicles ranging from a Mini
OL,18,FMetro to a decommissioned ambulance.
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                   G3/14
