OL,3,CThe women who were pivotal in allowing
OL,4,Cthe miners to strike
OL,6,F"We used to ferry the food then to the
OL,7,Fvarious sub stations. There were nine
OL,8,Fof those, and then it was from those
OL,9,Fthen that the miners picked up their
OL,10,Ffood parcels. It was an alternative
OL,11,Fwelfare state. We are talking about a
OL,12,Fsituation where there was no money
OL,13,Fcoming in. Absolutely zilch.. So you
OL,14,Fhave to say that the food parcels were
OL,15,Fvital."
