OL,3,CThe women who were pivotal in allowing
OL,4,Cthe miners to strike
OL,6,FThe hall in Onllwyn became the hub.
OL,7,FThere were fundraisers to put food on
OL,8,Fthe table. The hall was a sorting
OL,9,Fhouse, a headquarters where women,
OL,10,Fwith military precision, made up food
OL,11,Fparcels to feed 4,000 families across
OL,12,Fthe Neath and Swansea Valleys every
OL,13,Fweek.
OL,15,FChristine was already involved in
OL,16,Flocal politics and became the
OL,17,Ftreasurer of the Neath and District
OL,18,FMiners Support Group.
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                   G5/14
