OL,3,CThe women who were pivotal in allowing
OL,4,Cthe miners to strike
OL,6,FShe said: "We started picketing. You
OL,7,Fknow, we went all over the country
OL,8,Fwhen there was no need for pickets in
OL,9,FWales, but we went to a lot of pickets
OL,10,Faround the country. Some were alright.
OL,11,FSome were very nasty. You know, picket
OL,12,Flines weren't fun, but there was a lot
OL,13,Fof commitment.
OL,15,F"There was a lot of commitment from
OL,16,Fthe women on them. Sometimes, there
OL,17,Fwere a lot more women than men because
OL,18,Fthe men would be taken off the picket
OL,19,Flines and the women were replacing
OL,20,Fthem."
