OL,3,CThe women who were pivotal in allowing
OL,4,Cthe miners to strike
OL,6,FIt wasn't long before Ann was asked to
OL,7,Fspeak at mass rallies to galvanise
OL,8,Fsupport. Her first public speaking
OL,9,Fevent was in Swansea and she surprised
OL,10,Fherself at being able to do it.
OL,12,FFor many women, who hadn't had the
OL,13,Fopportunity to go to university, or
OL,14,Fwork outside of the home, the strike
OL,15,Fwas a turning point in their lives.
OL,16,FThey woke up to politics and new
OL,17,Fpossibilities.
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                  G10/14
